🌐 Networking Topology
Definition:
Network topology ka matlab hota hai arrangement/structure of devices (nodes) aur unka connection style ek network ke andar. Ye decide karta hai ki data ek device se dusre tak kaise travel karega.
🛠 Types of Network Topologies
🔗 1. Point-to-Point
Sirf 2 devices ke beech direct link hota hai.
Fast & simple communication.
Example: PC ↔ Printer
📏 2. Bus Topology
Saare devices ek single central cable (bus) se connected hote hain.
Cheap but agar cable damage ho jaye → pura network down.
Example: Purane Ethernet networks
🔄 3. Ring Topology
Har device apne 2 neighbors se connected hota hai → ek circular path banta hai.
Data ek hi direction me ghoomta hai (uni-directional / bi-directional).
Agar ek link toot jaye, pura ring disturb ho sakta hai.
⭐ 4. Star Topology
Saare devices ek central hub/switch se connect hote hain.
Agar ek node fail ho → baaki kaam karte rahte hain.
Agar hub fail ho gaya → pura network down.
Example: Modern LANs
🕸 5. Mesh Topology
Har device har dusre device se connected hota hai.
Super reliable (multiple paths available).
Lekin cost bahut zyada.
Example: Military communication networks
🌲 6. Tree Topology
Ek hierarchical structure jisme multiple Star networks ek backbone se connected hote hain.
Flexible aur scalable.
Example: Large organization networks
🔀 7. Hybrid Topology
Do ya zyada topologies ka combination.
Example: Star + Mesh, Star + Ring